data.name: optWGS.ToolTip
data.value: By international agreement, the 'standard' reference datum for altitude is MSL. Most GPS units display altitudes as MSL - even when the 'horizontal' datum is set to WGS84. Some GPS units allow you to output a spheroid height - but you should set it to output MSL heights. The spheroid height should only be used if the GPS unit only outputs spheroid altitudes.

data.name: label73.Text
data.value: This box is for any special messages or comments you think the person processing this report needs to know. Messages should be kept as short as possible. They will not be archived with the observations.
